heading_context: Delays to pension or benefit payments
chunks.html_content: If you live abroad and your payment is due in the same week as a US federal holiday, it could arrive one day late. This is because a US company processes these payments.
chunks.plain_content:
International Pension Centre
Delays to pension or benefit payments
If you live abroad and your payment is due in the same week as a US federal holiday, it could arrive one day late. This is because a US company processes these payments.

chunks.html_content:
You can read guidance on pensions and benefits including:

  • the basic State Pension, if you’re a man born before 6 April 1951 or a woman born before 6 April 1953
  • the new State Pension, if you’re a man born on or after 6 April 1951 or a woman born on or after 6 April 1953
  • claiming State Pension if you retire abroad
  • how to protect your State Pension and benefit entitlement if you move abroad, including voluntary National Insurance contributions
  • tax on your State Pension if you retire abroad
  • Incapacity Benefit
  • NHS advice about planning your healthcare abroad, including how to apply for an S1 form
